The paper discusses the technologies that drive the adoption of Multi-Access Edge Computing (MEC) in the context of 5G wireless systems. Network Function Virtualization (NFV) and Software Defined Networking (SDN) are key technologies in the networking domain, which fall under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Network Slicing is also a networking technology that enables the creation of virtual networks, which can be categorized under cs.NI or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Information Centric Networking (ICN) is a networking paradigm that focuses on content rather than hosts, which can be categorized under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) or cs.NI. Finally, Internet of Things (IoT) is a technology that enables the interconnection of physical devices, which can be categorized under cs.CE (Hardware and Embedded Systems) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
